{"type":"result","subtype":"success","is_error":false,"duration_ms":127745,"duration_api_ms":127698,"num_turns":5,"result":"","stop_reason":"end_turn","session_id":"4f5a16e5-4063-4819-b6da-8bf16a5d68b5","total_cost_usd":0.4640728999999999,"usage":{"input_tokens":6,"cache_creation_input_tokens":36733,"cache_read_input_tokens":132156,"output_tokens":2660,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":36733,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"},"modelUsage":{"claude-opus-4-6":{"inputTokens":6,"outputTokens":2660,"cacheReadInputTokens":132156,"cacheCreationInputTokens":36733,"webSearchRequests":0,"costUSD":0.36218925,"contextWindow":200000,"maxOutputTokens":64000},"claude-haiku-4-5-20251001":{"inputTokens":95,"outputTokens":5579,"cacheReadInputTokens":279124,"cacheCreationInputTokens":36785,"webSearchRequests":0,"costUSD":0.10188365,"contextWindow":200000,"maxOutputTokens":32000}},"permission_denials":[],"structured_output":{"summary":"All three amendments were verified against the actual codebase. Amendment fr-12-cda1336a identifies a confirmed missing terminal guard in the `Some(creation_hash)` branch of `safe_plan_hash_backfill`. Amendment fr-12-589cc81f correctly identifies that `deny_unknown_fields` on journal detail structs blocks forward-compatible repair. Amendment fr-12-cf3e1d18 traces the full call path showing how terminal replays reach the unguarded backfill, overlapping with but complementing fr-12-cda1336a.","votes":[{"amendment_id":"fr-12-cda1336a","decision":"accept","rationale":"Verified: the `Some(creation_hash)` branch (fs.rs:2637-2647) unconditionally sets `entry.plan_hash = Some(creation_hash.clone())` when the snapshot hash matches, with no `is_terminal()` check. The `None` branch (fs.rs:2648-2665) correctly returns false for terminal entries at line 2653. This asymmetry means a terminal entry with `snapshot_plan_hash_at_creation = Some(X)` and `plan_hash = None` will be incorrectly backfilled. The fix (add terminal guard to the `Some` branch or hoist it before the match) is straightforward and correct. This directly violates the stated contract that terminal replays must not auto-populate plan_hash."},{"amendment_id":"fr-12-589cc81f","decision":"accept","rationale":"Verified: both `StartJournalDetails` (model.rs:377) and `CompletionJournalDetails` (model.rs:412) carry `#[serde(deny_unknown_fields)]`. The code comments at lines 370-375 and 403-410 explicitly acknowledge the consequence: an older binary encountering unknown fields will fail deserialization, skip repair, and fall through to appending a duplicate event in `append_event_if_missing`. The merge implementations (fs.rs:2338-2407) use the generic `json_fill_none` helper which does not enforce field-level merge semantics. While the current behavior is data-safe (no corruption), it creates duplicate journal entries on binary downgrade and prevents any future field additions from being forward-compatible. If Amendment 1 previously required forward-compatible deserialization, this gap remains unaddressed."},{"amendment_id":"fr-12-cf3e1d18","decision":"accept","rationale":"Verified: `merge_attempt_entries()` (model.rs:328-330) copies `snapshot_plan_hash_at_creation` from secondary to merged entry when primary is None. `update_task_run()` (fs.rs:3379) calls `safe_plan_hash_backfill()` inside the already-finalized terminal replay branch (after the `entry.outcome.is_terminal()` check at line 3347). Because the `Some(creation_hash)` branch of `safe_plan_hash_backfill` lacks a terminal guard (the same bug as fr-12-cda1336a), the full path is: terminal replay → merge copies snapshot_plan_hash_at_creation → backfill mutates plan_hash from None to the snapshot hash. This violates the contract that terminal replays must preserve the caller-supplied None. While this overlaps with fr-12-cda1336a, it usefully documents the upstream call path that triggers the defect."}]},"fast_mode_state":"off","uuid":"1202a66d-e9a3-4efa-9b45-ed59d38941e2"}
